This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the problem of multiple access channels with interference. The use of lattice strategies is a key focus of the paper, which is a technique commonly used in information theory and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as these are all related to the topics discussed in the paper.
